node.text:
Originally was in my story but sharing this as a post. The more people are aware, the more they are willing to get involved.

When we think about children we are not just talking about school, but all the services and programs that go into keep a child safe and cared for while parents work. Over the last eight years I have had the pleasure of serving so many different families. It's been a blessing and I wouldn't change it for the world.

That being said, as a society we need to start understanding what it means to truly support our local communities and families. So much heartache and pain could be avoided if we took education, child care and family services seriously.

I understand the impact of the pandemic at this time and it's impact on programs, but let's be clear. The lack of real investment in family services was  an issue prior to Covid.

I say all this because I know people care. Now is the time to show it and be a part of the solution. 

#covid19
#endrant
#educational
#community

Riverside County health officials are giving out thousands of free facemasks until 11 a.m. today (Aug. 26) at the Menifee Valley campus of Mt. San Jacinto College as the county’s “Masks are Medicine” campaign winds down.

The campus is at 28237 La Piedra Road. Drivers are being asked to enter the campus off Antelope Road.

The county is closing out the “Masks are Medicine” campaign in which officials distributed 10 million masks in 30 days
